WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.383
Grace, mercy, and peace be unto you from our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ.

00:03.443 --> 00:07.046
And again, a portion of the Old Testament reading from Isaiah chapter two.

00:09.268 --> 00:15.194
In the last days, the mountain of the Lord's temple will be established as the highest of the mountains.

00:16.295 --> 00:20.319
It will be exalted above the hills, and all nations will stream to it.

00:21.400 --> 00:22.801
The Harry Nation will join me with the word of prayer.

00:25.083 --> 00:28.466
What God on this day, as we enter into this new season,

00:29.474 --> 00:34.699
We enter into the season of advent, of waiting, and longing, and looking for the coming of the Savior.

00:36.981 --> 00:54.919
Lord, let our prayer be one that echoes your promises given in Scripture, the promises of a new way of living, of a new life, all the promises that come with the Savior as Jesus comes into this world, bringing His own justice, bringing the love of the Father, and bringing forgiveness.

00:56.801 --> 00:58.002
Lord, let us put our hope

00:58.146 --> 01:05.978
on these promises once again this season as we look to the coming of the Savior and as we worship Him, we pray in Jesus' name.

01:06.799 --> 01:07.059
Amen.

01:07.880 --> 01:08.742
Irrigation may be seated.

01:14.530 --> 01:19.057
I hope you all had a very nice Thanksgiving weekend.

01:21.621 --> 01:27.730
Sure there was plenty of food on the table and hopefully family to gather around and time together.

01:28.642 --> 01:33.128
I was told though that I am not allowed to talk about a football game that took place on Friday evening.

01:33.148 --> 01:35.991
So I won't say anything about that.

01:40.677 --> 01:49.227
Thinking about meals like that though, Thanksgiving meals are Christmas meals, the holiday meals that we gather around for during this time of the year.

01:49.268 --> 01:57.778
I've always thought these meals are an opportunity to look into some of the great promises that we hold on to.

02:00.258 --> 02:03.541
Imagine a family gathered together around the table.

02:04.643 --> 02:14.012
And especially for a holiday like Thanksgiving, we have relative abundance that we should not forget in our country and in our lives.

02:15.894 --> 02:17.076
There's food.

02:18.657 --> 02:23.843
So often on our tables, like for these holiday meals, there's food and probably more than enough to go around.

02:24.623 --> 02:27.186
There's gathering of the people, the family.

02:27.426 --> 02:38.239
And it's almost like for a few minutes we can step away from some of the problems in the world and gather together and be together and just have conversation and hopefully everybody behaves themselves.

02:39.661 --> 02:43.686
It's a nice time, a good time to be together and to for a few minutes.

02:44.047 --> 02:53.358
Again, maybe forget about to walk away from to be separated from some of the normal worries and anxieties of the world around us.

02:54.800 --> 02:56.562
So there's food.

02:57.282 --> 03:02.769
There's community, family, gathering together of people, and there's a sense of home.

03:03.770 --> 03:19.751
Being in a place that is safe and secure, at least for a little while, a sense of being just together, home, being the place where we belong, the place where we are with others, who we love and who love us, where we are known, and where there's security, and each of these things.

03:22.314 --> 03:25.458
I think it's no mistake, no accident that

03:25.858 --> 03:38.040
It's some of our most cherished times, some of our favorite memories are those moments of being in that place, of being gathered together, of sharing in times like that, of the stories and conversations that take place.

03:39.062 --> 03:43.410
There's something in there that's deep and that we're made for, I think.

03:43.842 --> 03:50.171
And again, it's no accident because this is actually the picture we get at the end of the Bible of what God has in mind for His people.

03:50.231 --> 04:06.072
The stories from Revelation have the nations gathered together there around the feast that God Himself provides of good food, of choice wine, of the nations of the world, of the tribes, of all the peoples gathered together.

04:06.112 --> 04:08.295
And there is plenty.

04:08.335 --> 04:13.202
And there is community that is complete and full and there is

04:13.378 --> 04:14.941
a sense of being home.

04:15.763 --> 04:35.602
There's something we long for, and as we go through this season, as we go through the holidays, it should be a reminder for us of that deeper thing, that greater thing that we are made for, that there is something there that is very real, that we look to, that we hope for, that we long for, and that's what the promise of this season

04:36.322 --> 05:01.678
As we enter now into Advent, as we look towards Christmas, that's what the promise of this season is, is that there is a Savior coming into the world that will provide these good gifts for His people, for a world that is broken, that is tumultuous, that is weary, for people that are calling out, that are looking for a source of salvation, for hope, and something that is lasting.

05:02.760 --> 05:04.402
God's promises come in.

05:05.090 --> 05:10.056
God's Son comes into the world to be the promised one for His people.

05:11.638 --> 05:14.883
Isaiah chapter two foreshadows these things.

05:15.463 --> 05:27.218
Here at the very beginning of the book of Isaiah, Isaiah's got a vision of those final days of the last day of what this might look like in Isaiah's vision and his eyes and his seeing of it.

05:27.759 --> 05:33.266
And he says, come, let us go up to the mountain of the Lord, to the temple of the God of Jacob.

05:33.794 --> 05:40.261
He will teach us his ways so that we may walk in his paths, and the law will go out from Zion, the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.

05:41.342 --> 05:49.011
He will judge between nations, settle disputes for many peoples, and they will beat their swords and the plowshares and their spears and the pruning hooks.

05:49.631 --> 05:55.858
Nation will not take up sword against nation, nor will they train for war anymore.

05:57.740 --> 06:03.186
Isaiah's got a picture and a vision of the mountain of the Lord, of the nations being gathered

06:03.330 --> 06:05.713
together there around the mountain of the Lord.

06:06.074 --> 06:15.167
And what actually begins to happen as he sees it, as the nations are there, these things are so much different than they are in this life.

06:16.408 --> 06:24.480
And in this world, no longer do we go to earthly judges or arbiters or kings in order to get disputes settled.

06:24.800 --> 06:27.404
Now God settles the disputes for the peoples.

06:28.325 --> 06:31.730
He makes things right for them with his own righteousness.

06:32.642 --> 06:34.785
And now no longer is there training for war.

06:34.845 --> 06:37.028
The spears are set aside.

06:37.589 --> 06:38.850
The weapons are laid down.

06:38.890 --> 06:46.100
There's no longer any desire for those things because God has now made peace among the nations and peace for the peoples.

06:48.563 --> 06:50.365
This is the world that we long for.

06:50.385 --> 06:56.814
I would argue it's the world that we are made for, but we can see only now from a distance and we cannot get it yet.

06:56.914 --> 06:59.858
And Isaiah here is seeing it from a distance.

07:01.858 --> 07:05.023
Notably, Isaiah is seeing it from far off.

07:05.884 --> 07:08.988
Chapter one of Isaiah is very different than chapter two.

07:09.549 --> 07:18.081
Chapter two of Isaiah is hopeful he has this vision of this mountain of the Lord where the nations are streaming up and joining together with their God and Creator.

07:18.502 --> 07:24.210
But Isaiah chapter one is about the woes of a weary world.

07:25.218 --> 07:30.023
There, Isaiah says, hero heavens and give ear, oh earth, for the Lord has spoken.

07:30.524 --> 07:35.309
Children that I have reared and brought up, they are rebelling against me.

07:36.351 --> 07:41.196
The ox knows its owner and the donkey, it's master's crib, but Israel does not know my people.

07:42.738 --> 07:43.959
They do not understand.

07:46.642 --> 07:53.330
Isaiah is talking about the plight of the people of Israel, how they have wandered away from God.

07:54.018 --> 07:55.820
The result of that is going to be bloodshed.

07:55.861 --> 07:58.224
The result of that is going to be foreign armies coming in.

07:58.244 --> 08:04.853
The result of that eventually is going to be that they're taking captive in a foreign land once again all over again for the people of Israel.

08:05.173 --> 08:07.276
They have wandered away from the Lord their God.

08:07.296 --> 08:08.798
They have chosen other gods.

08:08.858 --> 08:10.381
They have worshiped idols.

08:10.421 --> 08:20.114
They are chasing after worldly things, wealth and power and all of those old idols that we still chase after today.

08:22.018 --> 08:23.921
So Isaiah chapter one is very honest.

08:24.362 --> 08:29.169
It's a look at the world, a weary world, and it's not that far off for us either.

08:29.770 --> 08:41.788
We easily can see it as well, reminded of this, even though maybe on Thursday, as we celebrated Thanksgiving, we got to separate just a little bit from the world than just the day before.

08:43.050 --> 08:50.962
I'm sure you saw the news of two National Guardsmen being shot in Washington, D.C., another one of these

08:51.618 --> 08:53.380
incidents that makes no sense to us.

08:54.242 --> 08:58.527
Another violent action that seems so senseless in this world, something that we mourn.

08:58.908 --> 09:08.061
Also, we know there's warfare happening other parts of the world, even as Russia and Ukraine are discussing peace, yet oil tankers are being sunk and aerosols are ongoing.

09:08.581 --> 09:09.543
It's continuing.

09:10.304 --> 09:18.535
We escape from it for a few minutes, but once we look back, once we turn our eyes, like from Isaiah chapter two, back to chapter one, we see the world as it really is.

09:19.877 --> 09:20.818
We become weary.

09:21.858 --> 09:24.562
And maybe closer to home, something that I know is a reality.

09:25.764 --> 09:38.746
For so many of us, even during a season of joy and light and goodness, as we do celebrate and gather with families, yet for so many, we look around and we realize there's someone who's not at the table that we wish that there was.

09:38.806 --> 09:43.333
Our hearts break just a little bit, and are not quite whole.

09:43.393 --> 09:48.882
Because of these realities of the hurt and the pain and the longing of a broken world,

09:50.946 --> 09:58.314
The Bible tells us all of this is the result of the fall of sin, of this chaos that still plagues us.

09:58.614 --> 10:02.298
And it is us ourselves who bring it about.

10:02.318 --> 10:11.608
It is we ourselves who make decisions and who take actions that are not always good for our neighbor, for those that we love.

10:11.628 --> 10:17.714
It is we ourselves who speak words that we shouldn't speak and think thoughts that we shouldn't think.

10:19.074 --> 10:33.877
It is we ourselves, it is us, it is the human condition in every one of us that as Isaiah here says in chapter one, my people Israel does not know, my people do not understand or follow after me.

10:33.937 --> 10:40.807
The children, my people that I have reared and brought up, they rebel against me.

10:43.030 --> 10:44.713
And so we know it is for us also.

10:45.674 --> 10:48.018
Every one of us in our own ways, in our own times,

10:48.674 --> 10:52.840
We also may find ourselves far from God.

10:53.741 --> 11:00.831
Doing things that we wish we didn't do as Paul talks about, do the things I wish I did not do, the things that I wish I would do I don't do.

11:00.851 --> 11:04.456
So we find ourselves far from God.

11:06.719 --> 11:14.049
But the season is one of hope and it is one of light and it is one of light in the darkness and of God's word coming forth.

11:15.171 --> 11:17.554
It's a season of hope and grace

11:17.858 --> 11:40.178
and love all the things that we talk about as we light the candles on the advent wreath of faith and trusting in God's promises of trusting in a God who can work in a weary world who has spoken into the plight of his people who sees and knows and when he sees the difficulty of his people as they call out to him God's own heart breaks.

11:41.474 --> 11:45.801
God's own heart breaks to the point that He sends His own Son from the heavenly realm.

11:45.841 --> 11:50.689
He sends Jesus down into the world to live among His hurting people.

11:52.972 --> 11:54.375
We give thanks for that this season.

11:55.697 --> 11:59.443
That Christ is coming to dwell among us, that He is with us.

11:59.843 --> 12:01.866
And that gives us hope in the here and now.

12:01.967 --> 12:03.689
Isaiah's promise is for the future.

12:05.953 --> 12:07.255
I'll close with that in just a minute.

12:07.295 --> 12:09.138
We look forward to that last day.

12:09.858 --> 12:13.323
that day when the nations go streaming towards the mountain of the Lord.

12:15.005 --> 12:18.951
But I also don't want us to overlook the day in which we live right now.

12:20.834 --> 12:26.902
We are not as people without hope because Christ has come to dwell among us.

12:28.224 --> 12:34.774
You can even think about him as being around the table with us on Thanksgiving or the other holiday feasts.

12:36.135 --> 12:37.938
He has come to be with us.

12:38.050 --> 12:39.471
This is what it means that he came into the world.

12:39.511 --> 12:53.105
He came to walk among his people and we see him in his ministry as he goes to the hurting, to the hungry, to the sick, to the dying and he reaches out to them and he lifts them up out of their sadness, out of their weakness, out of their sin and he gives them hope.

12:53.986 --> 12:59.492
A hope for a life that is to come, a hope that is new life in his name, a hope for this world.

13:01.894 --> 13:05.938
It's a hope that we so desperately need and that we long for and that we

13:06.626 --> 13:19.321
We work hard to keep in our minds to see the hope of the season and the hope of his promises, and then that it would so fill us that it would come through us and flow out of us as we live our lives also.

13:19.361 --> 13:20.822
This is our prayers, God's people.

13:20.842 --> 13:30.433
Let us turn away from our old selves, from the old Adam, from the old sinful self, and let us live in the light of his promises, of his goodness, of his grace, his mercy.

13:33.317 --> 13:34.578
So we go through this season.

13:34.658 --> 13:39.686
That is my prayer for our church, for the Christian church as a whole, but also for our church here.

13:39.706 --> 13:48.880
I think we are called to consider and pray for the world at large, for our church at large, but also, how can we embody this?

13:49.721 --> 13:56.411
How can we as individuals, how can we as a local church be this good news for the world, be this hope for the world?

13:56.431 --> 14:01.299
And I think it's by embracing both of these realities as we go through our lives, as we go through this season.

14:02.641 --> 14:03.602
First reality.

14:05.922 --> 14:12.754
as we are no strangers to the world is hurting and the world is weary and sometimes that's just me.

14:12.794 --> 14:13.976
I'm weary.

14:14.036 --> 14:15.719
I'm broken.

14:15.820 --> 14:16.340
I'm sick.

14:16.982 --> 14:28.562
I'm longing or I'm grieving and this is a reality and I hope as a church we can embrace that reality is important that we are there in order to receive those

14:28.674 --> 14:55.794
real issues of this life in this world that we that we mourn with those who mourn that we comfort those who need comforting that we speak words of encouragement to those who need encouraging but at the same time as we hold on to that reality that we never shy away from the other side of this reality and truth that we hold on to a great promise that has great power to come and speak into these hurting places of this world and of our lives.

14:57.602 --> 14:59.304
So that is where we need to get this picture.

15:00.505 --> 15:09.854
Imagine, as Isaiah sees it this morning, he looks to the mountain, he looks to the highest of the mountains, and there is the Lord's temple, and something strange is happening.

15:10.694 --> 15:15.599
Normally, in this world, he looked to the high mountains, and everything is falling down from them.

15:16.180 --> 15:20.203
He looked to the high mountains, and the waters always stream down the mountains.

15:20.824 --> 15:22.746
The rivers flow out of the mountains.

15:23.426 --> 15:25.408
Sometimes rocks are falling down the mountains.

15:25.428 --> 15:27.250
Sometimes the mountains are shrinking.

15:27.362 --> 15:28.083
over time.

15:28.463 --> 15:29.645
That's what happens in this world.

15:29.725 --> 15:35.173
Everything that is built up is slowly falling away and falling apart and decaying.

15:35.213 --> 15:37.896
Everything is just breaking down a bit.

15:40.119 --> 15:43.023
That's not what's happening on the mountain of the Lord as Isaiah sees it.

15:43.424 --> 15:46.448
The mountain of the Lord is rising, is growing, is becoming stronger.

15:46.488 --> 15:49.852
And not only that, but the nations are flowing up into the mountain of the Lord.

15:50.453 --> 15:53.077
The people are going up the mountain to meet with God.

15:53.097 --> 15:54.799
God is gathering the people together.

15:54.819 --> 15:56.882
He's raising them up.

15:58.722 --> 16:23.279
out of decay, out of despair, out of grief, out of longing, out of sickness, out of all of the things that plague the people of this world, God is raising them up and bringing them up His mountain to be with Him, to unite them together in the holy place, in His temple, in His presence, in His peace, in His goodness, in His love, and in His forgiveness.

16:24.901 --> 16:28.146
As we go through this season, I hope that we can do this well as a church.

16:28.258 --> 16:39.430
And we can keep this in mind to embrace the difficult reality of sin and the darkness of this world, but to not ever for a minute lose sight of the light that is streaming in.

16:39.450 --> 16:45.015
Of the promise of a God who is at the same time as we are dying, he is raising us up.

16:45.936 --> 16:49.039
The same time as this world is decaying, he is making it new.

16:49.080 --> 16:51.942
Same time as we are sinning.

16:51.963 --> 16:55.346
He is there with his forgiveness.

16:56.802 --> 17:07.576
So let us, as we worship Him this season, as we come into His house here, as we bring Him our praise, let us also know we are coming to the mountain of the Lord and daily and regularly through His Word and His promises.

17:08.657 --> 17:10.539
He is raising us up to be His people.

17:11.861 --> 17:17.368
He will carry us through this life, through death, and into the life that is to come.

17:18.229 --> 17:20.152
That is His promise for us in Jesus' name.

17:21.053 --> 17:23.416
Amen.

17:23.436 --> 17:25.138
I invite the congregation to stand at this time.

17:28.002 --> 17:32.626
May the peace of God which passes all understanding keep our hearts and minds in Christ Jesus our Lord.

17:33.611 --> 17:34.194
Amen.

